      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Specifically, the award was for the way we had integrated research, clinical practice and education, which in turns reflects QMU’s ethos of producing research that has a practical application and directly improves people’s lives.</p>
<p>The award was recognition that QMU’s research had generated new types of clinical assessment, which had then fed into clinical practice and had worldwide impacts. A key area highlighted in our award application was our work developing electropalatography (EPG).</p>
<p>Students were able to benefit from our research too, not just from input from research-active staff into their courses, but also from getting involved directly in aspects of research.</p>]]></Value>
