      <Value><![CDATA[In 2002, we were proud to receive the Queen’s University Prize for the clinical application of speech science. Specifically, the award was for the way we had integrated research, clinical practice and education, which in turns reflects QMU’s ethos of producing research that has a practical application and directly improves people’s lives.  The award was recognition that QMU’s research had generated new types of clinical assessment, which had then fed into clinical practice and had worldwide impacts. A key area highlighted in our award application was our work developing  electropalatography (EPG). Students were able to benefit from our research too, not just from input from research-active staff into their courses, but also from getting involved directly in aspects of research. ]]></Value>
